 :tx/rationale "EPIC design: Session Daemon (DAEMON EPIC). 7 core components: (1) Protocol: JSON-lines over Unix domain socket at .braid/braid.sock. Request={cmd, args, id}. Response={result, id, error?}. Streaming for long outputs. (2) Store holder: loads store once via DiskLayout::load_store, holds in memory, applies transactions incrementally via new Store::apply_tx method that inserts datoms + updates all 5 indexes in O(k) where k=datoms in tx (vs current O(n) from_datoms rebuild). (3) W_α: WorkingSet struct (INV-STORE-013) holds RFL-2 predictions, AR-2 traces, session telemetry in-memory. Not visible to merge. Flushed to .braid/.cache/working_set.bin on shutdown. (4) F(S) cache: Lazy<FitnessScore> invalidated when store mutates via knowledge-producing command (observe, harvest, transact) but NOT on operational telemetry (RFL-2, AR-2). (5) CLI thin client: detect socket, connect, send args as JSON, receive response, print. Fallback to embedded. (6) Lifecycle: auto-start on first braid command if .braid/ exists + no .braid/braid.sock. PID at .braid/braid.pid. 2h idle timeout. SIGTERM graceful. (7) Incremental Store: Store::apply_tx(&mut self, datoms: &[Datom]) inserts into datoms BTreeSet + updates entity_index, attribute_index, vaet_index, avet_index, live_view incrementally."
